values.description: The Wwise authoring application, a graphical user interface that centralizes all aspects of audio creation. The authoring application is required to edit Wwise projects and to generate SoundBanks.
The Wwise authoring application along with the debug DLLs and symbols for plug-in developers.

The C++ include files and several configurations of the compiled libraries and symbols, which are required by both the Unity and Unreal Integrations. SDK code samples and documentation are also included.
The Wwise User Guide PDF and the Wwise Help CHM.

The C++ source code of the Wwise SDK. A license for the Source Code is required per Deployment Platform, the license status can be viewed in the Customer Portal. Contact Audiokinetic sales for more information.
A LUA interpreter with Wwise SDK bindings.
The award-winning LIMBO game with complete Wwise project and companion documentation.
A full open-source game with C++ source code, Wwise project, and companion documentation.
A Wwise Project and companion documentation demonstrating Wwise features.

children.description: Enjoy a real-time and seamless connection between Nuendo 7 or its later versions and Wwise, via the Game Audio Connect feature.
children.name: Nuendo Game Audio Connect

children.description: McDSP brings a selection of their award-winning plug-ins directly to Wwise: FutzBox Lo-Fi Distortion and ML1 Mastering Limiter.
children.name: McDSP ML1, McDSP Futzbox

children.description: Microsoft Spatial Sound Platform APIs that enables spatial audio rendering on the Windows 10 and Xbox One platforms. Note that this plugin will no longer be required starting from Wwise 2021.1.0.
children.name: Microsoft Spatial Sound Platform

children.description: Auro-3D is the next generation three-dimensional audio standard. It provides the most immersive and natural realistic 3D sound experience.
children.name: Auro Headphone

children.description: Wwise Convolution lets you create convincing reverberation based on ambisonics impulse responses of real acoustic spaces, from the smallest room to the largest cathedral.
children.name: Wwise Convolution

children.description: iZotope offers a suite of their most popular sound design plug-ins for use directly within Wwise. The suite of Trash tools and Hybrid Reverb can take your sound design projects to the next level.
children.name: iZotope suite

children.description: Wwise Reflect is a geometry-informed plug-in that dynamically renders early reflections based on the proximity of the listener/emitter to reflective surfaces, such as walls, ceilings, and floors.
children.name: Wwise Reflect

children.description: REV 2, by Crankcase Audio, allows Wwise users to create extraordinarily authentic and powerful engine sounds via an advanced granular and auto-looping hybrid synthesis technique.
children.name: REV 2

children.description: Wwise SoundSeed is a family of specialized sound generators. Crafted with interactive audio in mind, these plug-ins help saving on CPU and memory while generating infinite variations.
children.name: Wwise SoundSeed Air, Wwise SoundSeed Impact
children.displayName: Wwise SoundSeed Air, Wwise SoundSeed Impact 2021.1.14.8108

children.description: Altiverb IRs is a library of 49 game-centric impulse responses provided by Audio Ease, which enhances the Wwise Convolution plug-in. Audio Ease has been traveling the world to record the acoustics of the very best sounding spaces.
children.name: Audio Ease Altiverb for Wwise Convolution
children.displayName: Audio Ease Altiverb for Wwise Convolution 2021.1.14.8108

children.description: SoundSeed Grain is a granular synthesizer which can be added to a Wwise project as a source Plug-In. It allows you to granulate and transform audio files with extreme flexibility.
children.name: Wwise SoundSeed Grain

children.description: The Resonance Audio Wwise integration includes plug-ins for spatial audio, optimized for performance and multi-platform support. Its advanced features go beyond basic 3D spatialization, providing powerful tools for accurately modeling complex sound environments.

eulas.displayContent: Some open source components are included as part of Resonance Audio. If you decide to use Resonance Audio, you must do so in accordance with the terms of the relevant open source licenses, which are located in the LICENSE.txt and NOTICE.txt files installed with the plug-in.

children.name: Resonance Audio SDK

children.description: This free plug-in uses the Steinberg Audio Stream Input/Output (ASIO) SDK in order to connect to ASIO compatible devices. It can be used as an Audio Device (output) or as a source plug-in (input).
children.name: Wwise ASIO

children.description: Wwise Motion plug-in adds the haptic feedback of a control interface.
children.name: Wwise Motion

children.description: This free mixer plug-in lets you to route and mix multiple buses with different channel configurations into a single output device. This is especially useful when dealing with an output device with many channels that require non-standard routing.
children.name: Wwise Channel Router

children.description: 68 high-definition outdoor impulse responses. Recorded and delivered in 192kHz to capture every characteristic detail of the respective location. For use with the Wwise Convolution Reverb plug-in. Compatible with all Wwise 2021.1.X versions.
